verbs.description: reenter (third-person singular simple present reenters, present participle reentering, simple past and past participle reentered)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To enter again; return into.
(transitive, computing) To enter again; retype, reinput.
examples: We had to reenter a day's worth of data into the system.

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive, engraving) To cut deeper where the aqua fortis has not bitten sufficiently.
